<HTML> <HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: The Mass Defense Committee</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../gifs/servbut.gif" ALT="SERVICES" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../gifs/masdefban.gif" ALT="THE MASS DEFENSE COMMITTEE" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE>The Mass Defense Committee is a subcommittee of the New York Chapter of <A HREF="./nlg.html">the National Lawyers Guild</A>.  The committee was organized in 1968 for the purpose of providing legal help to hundreds of students demonstrating and being arrested in the Columbia University student riots.<P><H3>Activities of the Committee</H3>Mass Defense Committee lawyers and law students:<UL>	<LI>assist in the planning of demonstrations	<LI>"legal-observe" at demonstrations	<LI>represent arrestees in court	<LI>and in other ways, attempt to help those that protest in New York.</UL><P><H3>Assistance from the Attorney of the Week</H3>If you require immediate assistance telephone the <A HREF="schedule.html">attorney "on call" for this week</A>.<P><H3>Attend Meetings of the Committee</H3>The committee meets once per month, and persons requesting the committee's assistance are welcome to attend <A HREF="schedule.html#meet">the next meeting</A>.<p><H3>Contact the Committee @masdef.org</H3>If you have a question or require information from the committee you can also <A HREF="mailto:atty@masdef.org?subject=For the Mass Defense Committee's attention">send us email</A>.<P></BLOCKQUOTE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER><HR><A HREF="../index.html"><IMG SRC="../gifs/homebar.gif" ALT="HOME" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5></A><A HREF="../serv/nlg.html"><IMG SRC="../gifs/nlgbar.gif" ALT="THE NATIONAL LAWYERS GUILD" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
