<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Commentary</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/commban.gif" ALT="Commentary" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD>Commentary on demonstrations and First Ammendment rights from newspapers and other publications.  Please <A HREF="mailto:news@masdef.org?subject=Commentary Submission">send us commentary</A> which you think would be appropriate here.<P><HR><BLOCKQUOTE><DL>
<P><DT><A HREF="petty=crimes.html"><b>NY Activists Increasingly Experience Substantial Detention</B></A>
<DD>AIDS activists recently arrested for grafitti protest were held over 24 hours.  It is
an increasingly common phenomenon in New York City's crackdown against "Quality of Life"
offenses.
<P><DT><A HREF="bad-food.html"><b>The Lawyer and the "Bad Food" Sign</B></A>
<DD>Lawyer's Food Protest Sign Above Restaurant Permitted.<P><DT><A HREF="stalking.html"><b>Anti-Abortion Protester Banned by "Stalking" Law</B></A>
<DD>Anti-Abortion demonstrators continue to require the definition of the outer limits of First Amendment activity.
<P><DT><A HREF="million.html"><B>Messages of Million-Man March Linger in Denver's Black Community</B></A>
<DD>The impact of a successful demonstration is usually measured by calculating whether or not the demonstrators persuaded others for their cause.  This article shows that a successful demonstration also unites and empowers the demonstrators.
<P><DT><A HREF="spy.html"><B>Portland Cops Caught Spying Illegally On Local Dissidents</B></A>
<DD>This was the first of a series of articles on police spying written by Mitzi Waltz for the journal PDXS. It's a chilling look at the type of police conduct many demonstrators suspect is going on but can't be sure.  It may be going on in all large cities. 
<P><DT><A HREF="buffer.html"><B>Supreme Court Abortion Protester Case to Affect All Demonstrators</B></A>
<DD>In conducting themselves in ways which threaten a significant right (the right to abortion), anti-abortion demonstrators have forced the courts to choose between favoring abortion clinic clients or free speech. As this article explains, the Supreme Court's acceptance of the Rochester and Buffalo "buffer zone" cases may result in free speech limitations. 
<P><DT><A HREF="stcruz.html"><B>Homeless Advocate is Target of Santa Cruz Repression</B></A>
<DD>Anti-Homeless Bias + Police Abuse = Advocate Under Attack
<P><DT><A HREF="flag.html"><B>Supporters Say Flag Amendment Will Return</B></A>
<DD>But Senate opposition may be deeper than close vote suggests.
<P><DT><A HREF="aclu.html"><B>ACLU Response to Denunciation of Student Demonstrators</B></A>
<DD>Mayor Giuliani could use a refresher course on the Bill of Rights.
<P><DT><A HREF="violence.html"><B>Link to Violence Could Put Curbs on Speech</B></A>
<DD>The recent spate of violence-first at abortion clinics, then atthe federal building in Oklahoma City-has triggered new debateover one of the oldest questions under First Amendment law: Whatis the relationship between speech and violence?
<P><DT><A HREF="clinics.html"><B>Does Freedom of Access to Clinic Act Infringe on Free Speech Rights?</B></A>
<DD>The ACLU believes the new law, as it is written, does not violate the First Amendment. 
<P><DT><A HREF="eric.html"><B>Eric Schissel's response to criticism of progressive activists</B></A>
<DD>A message to activists and feminists, socialists, gay-rights activists, environmentalists, labor-rights activists, anti-racists, anti-classists, radicals, idealists, and other crazy dreamers...
<P><DT><A HREF="xoncong.html"><B>The X-On Congress:  Indecent Comment On An Indecent Subject</B></A>
<DD>An article by Steve Russel, a retired state judge in Texas, that appeared in the February 8 issue of the American Reporter and has since been widely distributed on the net.

</DL></BLOCKQUOTE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER><HR><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/homebar.gif" ALT="HOME" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5></A><A HREF="../reps/index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/repsbar.gif" ALT="REPORTS" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5></A><A HREF="../noti/index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/notibar.gif" ALT="NOTICES" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
