<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Legal Materials</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/refsbut.gif" ALT="REFERENCES" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/legaban.gif" ALT="Legal Materials" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><UL type=I><FONT SIZE="4">	<LI><A HREF="#decis"><B>Court Decisions</B></A><P>		<LI><A HREF="#paper"><B>Sample Motions</B></A><P>	<LI><A HREF="#trans"><B>Transcripts from Court Appearances</B></A><P>		<LI><A HREF="#law"><B>Pertinent Statutes</B></A>	</FONT></UL><P><HR><H2><A NAME="decis">Court Decisions</A></H2><BLOCKQUOTE>The following court decisions involve issues which frequently arise in connection with demonstration cases.  If you think a decision relates to your case and favors you, take the decision to court and tell the judge about it.<P><B>Resisting Arrest / Going Limp</B><P><UL>	<LI><A HREF="bauer.html">People v. Bauer</A><BR>	Going limp at the time of arrest <i>DOES</i> constitute Resisting Arrest.<P>		<LI><A HREF="mcdanie.html">People v. McDaniel</a><BR>	Going limp at the time of arrest <i>DOES NOT</i> constitute Resisting Arrest.<P>		<LI><A HREF="amybeth.html">People v. Amy Beth</A><BR>	Going limp at the time of arrest <i>DOES NOT</i> constitute Resisting Arrest. <P>		<LI><A HREF="stephen.html">People v. Stephen</A><BR>	Where officer lacked probable cause for arrest, Resisting Arrest charge must be dismissed.<P></UL><B>Disorderly Conduct</B><P>	<UL>	<LI><A HREF="carcel.html">People v. Carcel</A><BR>	Only partially blocking pedestrian traffic does not constitute Disorderly Conduct.<P>		<LI><A HREF="cody.html">People v. Cody</A> also <A HREF="stephen.html">People v. Stephen</A><BR>	A vulgar statement alone directed at a police officer does not constitute Disorderly Conduct.<P>	<LI><A HREF="dietze.html">People v. Dietze</A><BR>	Vulgar, derisive or provocative speech is protected by the First Amendment unless it presents a clear and present danger of some substantive evil.<P>	<LI><A HREF="mackinney.html">MacKinney v. Nielsen</A><BR>	An arrestee is entitled to verbally protest his or her arrest.<P>	<LI><A HREF="tarka.html">People v. Tarka</A><BR>	A summons for disorderly conduct must in some way specifically allege that arrestee intended to inconvenience or alarm others.<P>	<LI><A HREF="daewoo.html">Dae Woo Kim v. City of New York</A><BR>	New York City's "unreasonable noise" prohibition is found unconstitutional.<P></UL><B>Dismissal in the Interests of Justice</B><P><UL>		<LI><A HREF="amybeth.html">People v. Amy Beth</A><BR>	Irish gay and lesbian group not entitled to dismissal in interests of justice in connection with St. Patrick's Day Parade protest.<P></UL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR><H2><A NAME="paper">Sample Motions</A></H2><BLOCKQUOTE>The following are motions which attorneys submitted to attempt to obtain dismissals of demonstration cases.  Although you could not use the motions as they appear you could use the reasoning for your own oral or written motions if you have similar situations.<P><B>Motion to Dismiss:</B><UL>	<LI><A HREF="insuff.html">due to insufficiency of prosecutor's information</A><P>	<LI><A HREF="speedy.html">speedy trial-police failure to appear in Summons Part within 30 days</A><P>	<LI><A HREF="intjust.html">in the interests of justice</A><P></UL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR><H2><A NAME="trans">Transcripts From Court Appearances</A></H2><BLOCKQUOTE>The following transcripts of court proceedings will give you an idea of what is said in court in the average demonstrator case.<P><UL>	<LI>under construction</UL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR><H2><A NAME="law">Pertinent Statutes</A></H2><BLOCKQUOTE>Below are the sections of the New York State Penal Law which most frequently come into play relative to demonstrator arrests.<P><UL><LI><A HREF="24020.html">240.20  Disorderly Conduct</A><P><LI><A HREF="14005.html">140.05  Trespass</A><P><LI><A HREF="14010.html">140.10  Criminal trespass in the third degree</A><P><LI><A HREF="20530.html">205.30  Resisting arrest</A><P><LI><A HREF="24005.html">240.05  Riot in the second degree</A><P><LI><A HREF="24006.html">240.06  Riot in the first degree</A><P><LI><A HREF="24008.html">240.08  Inciting to riot</A><P><LI><A HREF="3505.html">35.05  Justification; generally</A><P><LI><A HREF="19505.html">195.05  Obstructing governmental administration in the second degree</A></UL></BLOCKQUOTE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER><HR><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/homebar.gif" ALT="HOME" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5></A><A HREF="../manu/index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/manubar.gif" ALT="MANUAL" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5></A><A HREF="../orgs/index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/orgsbar.gif" ALT="ORGANIZATIONS" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
