<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: German Police Attack Hungerstrikers</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD>
<H3>German Police Attack Hungerstrikers</H3>
<PRE>Today, Wednesday, June 26 1996, the German police attacked the hungerstrikers in
Cologne. More than sixty people were brutally harassed and arrested. Most of
them were in Hungerstrike for 20 days.

The comrades in Cologne  started a hungerstrike on June 6 in solidarity with the
hungerstrike of the political prisoners in Turkey, united in the "Comity for the
Freedom of  the Political prisoners".

The demands in Turkey as well in the numerous solidarity hungerstrikes in Europe
are: * 1. The so called May 6 Decree must be withdrawn. * 2. All isolation
prisons, like the one in Eskisehir, must be closed
      down.
 * 3. The prisoners must be allowed adequate medical treatment.
 * 4. The prisoners must have the opportunity to attend their own trials.
 * 5. The policy of systematic abuse must come to an end.
 * 6. The repression against relatives and lawyers must be stopped.

In Cologne, Germany, the German state acted like a watchdog from the fascist
Turkish state.  Many people were wounded. One person was wounded that heavy that
he had to be transported to the hospital with an ambulance. Also two German
lawyers, who protested the violent, unjustified behaviour against the weakened
hungerstrikers were arrested as well.

GERMANY IS BEHAVING ITSELF WORSE THAN TURKEY

In Turkey, the people know the real face of the enemy of the people. In Turkey
fascism is open and clear to see for everybody. Germany is pretending that it is
a democracy that learned from it's fascist history. In fact it is protecting the
fascist regime in Turkey, acting like a major supporter of the fascist
oppression as felt in the Turkish prisons and the ordinary civil society in
Turkey.

WE CALL ON THE INTERNATIONAL SOLIDARITY!

THE POLITICAL PRISONERS IN TURKEY NEED YOUR SOLIDARITY!

It looks like it is going to be a very hard struggle that may costs precious
live. The political prisoners in Turkey have shown their determination on
numerous occasions. They are not going to give in in this struggle for live.

LONG LIVE THE INTERNATIONAL SOLIDARITY!

DOWN WITH FASCISM!

FREE THE COLOGNE 60!

LONG LIVE THE PEOPLES RESISTANCE!

VOICE YOUR PROTEST!

Protest faxes:

Germany:

Head of Police: #  49-221-22 98 922
Head of  State: #  49-221-14 731
State Prosecuter: # 49-221-47 74 050

Turkey:

Minister of Justice, M. Agar: # 90-312-417 39 54
Minister of Internal Affairs, U. Guney:# 90-312-418 17 95

------------------------------------------
Visit <a href="HTTP://WWW.xs4all.nl/~ozgurluk">http://www.xs4all.nl/~ozgurluk</a>
For regular news and information
about the classwar in Turkey and Kurdistan

