<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Protest Site in Dispute at Repub Convention</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD>
<H3>Republican Convention -- Protesters Moved Away Already</H3>
<PRE>                        *GOP Convention Protests Moved*

SAN DIEGO -- Under threat of lawsuits from the city and protesters,
Republican officials ``reluctantly accepted'' a compromise
demonstration area Friday for this summer's GOP convention, the
Associated Press reports.

The new, three-acre site is farther than a spot favored by police
and the American Civil Liberties Union across from the San Diego
Convention Center. But it's closer than one preferred by the
Republican National Committee.

``We could have ended up in a three-way litigation between the
city, the ACLU and the RNC,'' City Manager Jack McGrory told the
AP. ``I think once (the RNC) saw that we were taking a firm
position on this, they really didn't have much choice but to go
along with the alternative.''

The convention center is within sight of the protest area, now a
patch of parking lots and storage yards. With microphones and
speakers, an estimated 15,000 protesters will have no problems
being heard by delegates, he said.

Still, activists reacted less than enthusiastically and said they
have not yet decided whether to sue for another site.

``We're going to be looking at the proposed alternatives in the
next few days and then decide what the next step will be,'' Jordan
Budd, managing attorney for the local ACLU, told the AP. ``A
lawsuit is clearly an option.''

Brenda Schumacher, an organizer of a massive gay and lesbian
protest, criticized the city for caving into the Republican
demands.

``The city is placating the Republican National Committee and
selling our constitutional rights down the river,'' she said.</PRE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
