<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Vigils and Arrests at SF Food Not Bombs</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD>
<H3>Vigils and Arrests at SF Food Not Bombs</H3>
<PRE>Tuesday, June 18, 1996

SF Food Not Bombs member Keith McHenry was arrested today for serving =
food in front of the Hall of Justice, 850 Bryant Street, San Francisco.

Oatmeal was being served in violation of a long standing court order, =
prohibiting Food Not Bombs from serving food in the city without a =
permit.  After over 100 attempts to get a permit (all denied under the =
Jordan administration without stated reason), the city dismantled the =
permit process and rescinded the requirement to have a permit to serve =
food in public.  The court order still stood, however, and was used as a =
pretext to harass and arrest members of Food Not Bombs.  Despite over =
1000 arrests in an organization that, at its height, never had more than =
50 or 60 active members, Food Not Bombs never stopped serving food to =
the homeless seven days a week.

Under the new administration of Mayor Willie Brown, the harassment and =
arrests of FNB members had ceased.  The serving of oatmeal in front of =
the Hall of Justice had begun in solidarity with Robert Norris Kahn, who =
was sentenced to 59 days in jail for serving soup and bagels to the =
homeless in violation of the court order.  His arrest had occurred under =
the Jordan administration.

The vigil will continue mornings at 9AM, but it will be move to the =
temporary location of the San Francisco City Hall:  the War Memorial =
Building, 401 Van Ness, San Francisco. =20


To contact Food Not Bombs:  415-985-7087
<a href="http://www.webcom.com/~peace/PEACTREE/stuff/stuff/HOMEPAGE.html">http://www.webcom.com/~peace/PEACTREE/stuff/stuff/HOMEPAGE.html</a>

Volunteer are needed for cooking, transporting, and serving food, for =
volunteering kitchens, for the vigil, and other actions.</PRE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
