<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Activists Force Removal of Nazi School Governor</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD>
<H3>Activists Force Removal of Nazi School Governor</H3>
<PRE>Hull ( UK )

After a prolonged and concerted effort, a coalition of anti nazi
groups trade unionists and parents has forced the resignation of a
nazi, school governor.  Right-wing governor Michael Cooper has
resigned from the board of two city schools.

Last night ( Thursday 13, 06, 96, ) more than 200 activists picketed a
governors meeting at Andrew Marvel school, demanding the removal of
Mr. Cooper from the governing body of school and also from the Griffin
primary school.  Mr. Cooper a one time candidate for the National
Front in local elections and more recently a candidate for the
far-right extremist National Democratic party in by elections in
Yorkshire, had been elected to the board of governors at both schools
without contest.

Once elected Cooper was in position to influence the direction of the
school through budgetary constraint and manipulation.  The ease in
which the likes of Cooper and his cronies can gain positions of
influence should be a warning to all community activists, vigilance
and commitment to local governing bodies is the only way to deter the
nazi's.  Removing these nazi's is far harder than excluding them in
the first place.

Congratulations to all involved.

Unison, GMB, ANL, SWP (HULL ), Millitant, Bilton PTA, etc...

Regards Bill 101555.1565@compuserve.com

