<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Solidarity Action for Mumia at Dannish Parliament</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD>
<H3>Solidarity Action For Mumia Abu-Jamal At The Danish Parliament</H3>
<PRE>

This is from Danish television news on the evening of June 12th:

     On Wednesday, June 12, 1996, three activists entered the
Danish Folketinget (the parliament), showed their IDs, and stated
that they where visiting the library. Instead, they went to the
empty offices of a right-wing party, Venstre, broke into it,
nailed the doors shut from the inside, and barricaded them with
the furniture of the office.
     In the office, the activists destroyed furniture and
equipment, such as computers. Through the window they chanted
slogans to free Mumia Abu-Jamal and waved a banner. Outside, a
fourth activist distributed leaflets. According to Danish
television, the chairman of Venstre called his office when he
heard of the occupation, to ask the activists not to damage one
of his pipes which he had left in the office (!). The activists,
according to the chairman, said they would throw the pipe out the
window unless they were given a helicopter to take them to Cuba.
(For anyone not familiar with Danish activists: this was a joke).
     After a while, riot police broke through the barricaded
doors and arrested the three activists. The fourth outside was
also arrested.

