<H3>Arrests Following Flag-Burning Protest</H3>
<PRE>  Former Black Panther Militia leader Mmoja Ajabu and 2 other
militia  members were in jail today after a scuffle with police
during Olympic torch and flame ceremonies on the Circle tues night.
  The trio allegedly tried to set fire to a U.S. flag in protest
of the  pending execution of convicted killer Tommie Smith, police
said.   Ajabu , Donald Howell, and Roy Robertson each wete charged
with 2 counts of a rson, resisting law enforcement and battery on
a police officer, Ajabu and Robertson were also charged with
disorderly conduct. Howell was charged with a violation of the 1935
Firearms act.
