<H3>Boulder Earth First! Pickets Mitsubishi</H3>

<PRE>Daily Camera, Boulder, Colo. 

Knight-Ridder/Tribune Business News 

May 21--MITSUBISHI PROTEST: Environmental activists picketed outside Boulder 
Mitsubishi Inc. Monday to protest Mitsubishi's logging practices. The picket 
took place as part of a national Day of Action to End Corporate Dominance of 
the Earth, led locally by Boulder Earth First! The group claims Mitsubishi, 
as one of the world's largest logging and timber importing companies, has been 
destroying rainforests around the globe. Boulder Earth First! also alleges that 
Mitsubishi is under criticism from U.S. women's organizations for its treatment 
of employees who have filed sexual harassment lawsuits against the company. 

The group hopes the protest will help educate consumers about the ongoing boycott 
of Mitsubishi by the Rainforest Action Network. 

But Lee Fishbein, general manager of the Mitsubishi dealership, said the protest 
was less than effective. "They (the protestors) didn't even know what they were 
talking about," Fishbein said. "We actually had some people call who drove by 
and saw it to tell us they support us." Fishbein said about a dozen people turned 
out for the protest.

Mike Lewinski has set up a web page responding to the manager's quote at
<A HREF="http://bcn.boulder.co.us/environment/earthfirst/befmitsu.html">http://bcn.boulder.co.us/environment/earthfirst/befmitsu.html</A> </PRE>
</TD>
