<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: More Brutal Protest Arrests in Turkey</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><H3>More Brutal Protest Arrests in Turkey</H3><PRE>ISTANBUL, May 18 (Reuter) - Turkish police have arrested dozens ofpeople including a senior French trade unionist taking part in acandlelit vigil in Istanbul for missing people, human rights activistssaid on Saturday.Turkey's state-run Anatolian news agency said 20 people had beenarrested at the protest on Friday, but a French human rights group putthe number at about 40.The left-wing Movement Against Racism and for Friendship Between Peoples(MRAP) said in Paris that police ``brutally attacked'' a ceremonyorganised by mothers and spouses of people who had disappeared. It saidthose arrested included Frenchman Vincent Raynal, a senior official ofthe Communist-linked CGT union, and an unidentified British womanteacher. Raynal and others were injured by police, it added.The French group said in a statement: ``MRAP energetically protestsagainst the unacceptable attitude of the Turkish government which triedto prevent the holding of an international conference on disappearedpeople which was both authorised and long-scheduled.''MRAP said that among foreign delegates to the conference were members ofAmnesty International, of the German Greens party and activists fromLatin America and former Yugoslavia.Turkish police declined comment on the arrests.The Anatolian news agency reported that several journalists covering theprotest were held briefly by police.</PRE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR