<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Rock Against Racism Snubbed</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><H3>N.Y. Federal Judge Upholds Snub of Rock Against Racism Event</H3><PRE>May 17thNew York Federal Judge Upholds Parks Dept Snub of Rock Against RacismToday Judge John Keenan, a United States federal judge, issued adecision refusing to order the New York City Parks Department to issue aspecial events permit for Rock Against Racism, an annual musical andinformational event, this year scheduled for May 18th.RAR had been promised the permit for Washington Square Park in GreenwichVillage, by Thomas Kenny, Parks Director of Permits, on April 24th, butthe Parks Dept. reversed itself on May 7th after two local politicianswrote letters against RAR.  The letters referred to noise, damage andarrests arising out of an event sponsored by another organization, CuresNot Wars, in the same park, on May 4th.  The Parks reversal on May 7thcaught organizers Alan Thompson and Dana Beal, who had planned andpublicized the event for May 18th, by surprise.  After attempts atnegotiating the situation failed, on May 15th Rock Against Racismbrought a federal suit agaist Parks Commissioners Henry Stern and AdrianBenepe alleging denial of First Amendment rights and requesting aninjunction requiring the Parks Department to issue the permit.Yesterday, on May 16th, Judge Keenan held a hearing on the matter andheard the testimony of Mr. Thompson.  During the hearing, which wasattended by community residents, Judge Keenan appeared more concernedabout the possibility of noise complaints than free speech rights.The court's decision meant that Rock Against Racism, which featurespoets, a wide variety of musicians and speakers, will be silenced forthe first time since 1979.For further information, call Dana Beal, 212-677-7180</PRE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
