<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: More Protest in E. Timor</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><H3>More Protest in E. Timor</H3><PRE>Yesterday, in the city of Baucau, east of Dili, hundreds ofyoung Timorese marched through the streets in protest against killingof one of their companions on Thursday by Indonesian soldiers."They marched in protest from the new part of the city to theold part.  There must have been about a hundred demonstrators", saidone resident, quoted by Reuters.  The same source reported that theydemonstrated for about 3 hours before breaking up.East Timor's police chief, Andreas Sugianto, confirmed that ademonstration had in fact taken place after mass.  However, he putthe number of protesters at just 30 to 60 people.  He told Reuters:"We just dispersed them - there were no arrests made or legal actiontaken."** End of text from cdp:reg.easttimor *************************************************************************This material came from PeaceNet, a non-profit progressive networkingservice. For more information, send email to <A HREF="mailto:peacenet-info@igc.apc.org">peacenet-info@igc.apc.org</A>***********************************************************************</PRE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
