<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Peace Activists Disrupt Nevada Nuclear Tests</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><H3>PEACE ACTIVISTS DISRUPT NEVADA NUCLEAR TESTS</H3><PRE>Accounted by David KupferPromoters of peace continue to have an active presence at the gatesoutside the entrance to the Nevada Test Site 65 miles outside of LasVegas, Nevada. While the Conprehensive Test Ban Agreement was signed bythe President and has been in place since 1993 , a new set of  sixunderground nuclear explosions scheduled to take place over two years atLyner facility by the Federal Dept. of Energy were  at Nevada Test Site,designed to learn the impact of aging plutonium on nuclear weaponsefficiency, were scheduled.These new tests fly directly in the face of the CTB and the stated USGovt aim to end and reverse the arms race. As many veteran activistsnoted this past weekend, our government cannot in good conscienceprepare for peace and war simultaneously, and maintain any character andintegrity in the international community. Peace activists feel thatthese tests are absolutely unneccessary, only excuses for the embattledTest Site scientists to hang onto some thread of legitimacy andjustifying their now clearly uneeded existence at the weapons lab.On Good Friday, 38 men and women crossed the cattle guard on the road toMercury, onto Western Shoshone land illegally occupied by Department ofEnergy, and were immediately arrested for trespassing. On Easter Sundaymorning, following a march and eucuminical service at the gates, morethan 80 peace promoters were arrested for crossing over cattle guardonto federal DoE land illegally. learn that the first such test,origially scheduled for June, had been delayed for 8 weeks. However, thetimeline for the first detonation was again postponed until December bythe Clinton administation, thereby negating the issue from being broughtup in the upcoming Presidential campaign.On Monday morning, April 8,  Peace Activists interupted the normalactivities at the Test Site with sophisticated road blockades for fivehours. Three truckloads of nuclear waste were amoung the hundreds ofvehicles that were prevented from entering the facility.  Organizerspointed to the trucks vulnerability and exposure as another of the manyrisks in the nuclear chain, which currently includes plans to transportwaste from around the world to Nevada.Western Shoshone Spiritual Leader Corbin Harney expressed his gratitudefor peace activists' efforts to close the Test Site and raise theawareness of his peoples struggle against the U.S. occupation of theirancestoral homeland.  "We must unite ourselves against the destructionof our Mother Earth and all the living things that depend on her forsurvival."  Harney said while speaking to television news reporters "Ireally appreciate what the people are doing here."Prior to the five day encampment and civil disobedience at the NevadaTest Site,  a three day Nuclear Abolition Summit was held at theUniversity of Nevada Las Vegas.  Over 150 attendees from  Germany, NewZealand, Sweden, and elseware around the world, including Habakashasurvivors of the Hiroshima and Nagasaki atomic bombings disscussed plansand laid out strategy for a united global effort to abolish nuclearweapons by the year 2000.For further infromation, contact:  HEALING GLOBAL WOUNDS at (202)588-0912.** End of text from cdp:headlines *****************************************************************************This material came from PeaceNet, a non-profit progressive networkingservice.  For more information, send a message topeacenet-info@igc.apc.org***************************************************************************</PRE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
