<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Bahrain Torture of Demonstrators</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><H3>Bahrain Torture of Demonstrators</H3><PRE>                       CHILD CONCERN                    Case BHR 010496.CC                            and                      Case BHR 010496The  International Secretariat of OMCT/SOS-Torture requests your  URGENTintervention in the  following  situation  in Bahrain.Brief description of the situation: The  Bahrain Human RightsOrganisation (BHRO), a member  of the network, has expressed its graveconcern over the great number  of  arbitrary  detentions (includingchildren)  in Bahrain and the potential exposure of prisoners totorture. The  concern  is all the more urgent given the two  decreesissued  on 20 March 1996, which increase the power  of  the StateSecurity Court. This court may base its  convictions on  writtenstatements  and testimonies  of  the  Security Intelligence Section(SIS) so that it can rapidly treat all cases related to recent protests.BHRO  has  expressed its particular concern over  the  high number  ofchildren among the detained.  The following  are some  of  the available names of  children  arrested  and detained  between  22  and 27 March1996:  Nadia  Issa  Ali Hassan  (16), Khadija Ahmed Ali (16), Khatoon Sa'ed  (16), Massoma  Sayyed-Jaffar  (15),  Zainab Sayyed-Falah (16),Kaltham  Sayyed-Adnan (16), Kholood  Jawad  Ali (16),  Ali Mulla-Jawad (16), Mallik Mohed Al-Arab  (16),  Fadhel  Ali Juma  (17), SadiqueSolayman Al-Setry (17), Hussain  Abdul- Wahab Al-Khayyat  (15),  JafferYahya  (17),  Sadig  Ahmed Kadhem  (16), Abdulla Issa Khamees (13),Abbas Ahmed  (15), Hussain Hassan (15) and Jaffer Ali Mohammed (15).All  the  above  have  been detained for  participation  indemonstrations.The  International Secretariat notes that Bahrain is  State party  tothe Convention on the Rights of the Child  whose articles  37  and  40,amongst others,  provide  that  the arrest, detention or imprisonment ofa child shall be  used only  as  a measure of last resort, and thatchildren  have the  right  to be presumed innocent until proven guiltyby law. Recent  arrests  and  detentions  of  children are therefore in full breach of Bahrain's commitment  to  the Convention on the Rights ofthe Child.Case BHR 010496 =20 BHRO  has also expressed its grave concern for thephysical and  psychological integrity of 63 people detained  in  thelast  weeks. A full list of the names and dates of  arrests is availablefrom the International Secretariat.At least 4 detainees run the risk of execution by the State SecurityCourt: Ali Ahmed Al-Asfoor, Ahmed Khalil  Ibrahim Al-Kattab,  QamberKhamis  Qamter  and  Khaleel Ebraheem Abdulla  Khamees, all labourers.They were  arrested  among others  in  connection with the burning of arestaurant  in Sitra  on 13 March 1996. The fire led to the death ofseven Bengali  expatriates  living in  the  upper  floor  of  therestaurant.  A  previous  statement  by  the  Ministry of Interior said that the persons who had started  the  fire were not identified. Three detainees  were sentenced on 27 March  1996  by  the State SecurityCourt for their involvement in the protests against the Al-Khalifaregime. The court sentenced Ali Adel Al-Tall to 12 years of imprisonmentand a fine of $ 80'000. The two others were sentenced to 5 yearsimprisonment.Within  the  general  deterioration  of  the  human  rights situation inBahrain,  the  International Secretariat seriously  fears  that theexecution of Issa  Ahmed  Qamber which  took  place on 26 March 1996after an  unfair  trial might  set  the  precedent for further deathsentences  and executions.Action requested:Please write to the Bahrain authorities urging them to:i.  order  the immediate release of all children,  if  they    are  still  detained, and guarantee their physical  and    psychological integrity;ii. guarantee  the physical and psychological integrity  of    all other people detained;iii.order  the immediate release of all detainees  if  they    are  detained without valid charges or, if such charges    exist,  bring  them  before a competent  and  impartial    tribunal and guarantee their procedural rights  at  all    times;iv. guarantee  a  full,  impartial and  exhaustive  enquiry    into  the facts, identify those responsible, bring them    to trial and apply the  penal, civil and/or    administrative sanctions provided by legislation;v.  ensure  in  all circumstances respect for human  rights    and  fundamental freedoms in accordance  with  national    laws and international standards.Addresses:His Highness Shaikh =92Issa Bin Salman Al Khalifa, Office  ofHis  Highness  the  Amir, P.O. Box 555,  The  Amiri  Court,Rifa=92a Palace, Bahrain.Fax : + 973 668884. Telex : 8666 Qasar BN; 8500 Qasar BNHis  Excellency Shaikh Khalifa Bin Salman Al Khalifa, PrimeMinister,P.O. Box 1000, al-Manama, Bahrain.Telex : 9336 PROM BN or 7889 PMPO BNHis  Excellency  Shaikh Muhammad Bin  Khalifa  Al  Khalifa,Minister of Interior, P.O. Box 13, al-Manama, Bahrain.Fax : + 973 276765 or 290526. Telex : 9572 PSMKT BN OR 8333ALAMAN BNGeneva 01 April 1996Kindly inform us of any action undertaken quoting the  codenumber of this appeal in your reply.Ben SchonveldProjects ManagerOMCT/SOS-TortureCase Postale 119Rue de Vermont 37-39CH-1211Tel:4122 733 3140Fax:4122 733 1051** End of text from cdp:pn.alerts *****************************************************************************This material came from PeaceNet, a non-profit progressive networkingservice.  For more information, send a message to peacenet-info@igc.apc.org***************************************************************************</PRE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
