<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Twelve Arrested in March 13th Demo at Brooklyn DA's Office</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><H3>TWELVE ARRESTED IN MARCH 13TH DEMO AT BROOKLYN DA'S OFFICE</H3><PRE>On Wednesday, March 13, 1996, family members of police murdervictims Anibal Carrasquilo Jr. and Yong Xin Huang staged sit-in insidethe office of Brooklyn District Attorney Charles Hynes. Accompani ed bymembers of the National Congress for Puerto Rican Rights and theCommittee Against Anti-Asian Violence, the parents and siblings of thesetwo young men, who died at the hands of the police, ent ered the officeof Charles Hynes to demand:1)  That Brooklyn DA Charles Hynes reconvene a Grand Jury to indict POSteven Mizrahi for the brutal murder of Yong Xin Huang(young-shin-hwang), a 16-year old Chinese American youth from Bushwick Brooklyn.2)  That Brooklyn DA Charles Hynes reconvene a Grand Jury to indict POMarco Calderon for the brutal murder of Anibal Carrasquilo (a-KNEE-bal kar-ra-SKEE-yo), a 21-year old Puerto Rican youth from Flatbush,Brooklyn.Anibal Carrasquillo was shot and killed by PO Marco Calderon inFlatbush, Brooklyn on January 22, 1995.  Although Calderon originallyclaimed to have shot Anibal in the chest and stomach, an officialautopsy revealed that he was shot in the back only. Anibal posed nothreat to Calderon -- he was unarmed and his back was turned to thepolice officer.  Furthermore, the family charges that Anibal's body wasremoved from the original site of the murder and placed in a dark alleyin order to make the shooting appear more "legitimate."  Despite thebullets in the back, the DA's office of Charles Hynes failed to indictMarco Calderon.Yong Xin Huang was shot and killed by PO Steven Mizrahi in SheepsheadBay, Brooklyn on March 24, 1995.  Yong Xin was shot point-blank in theback of the head.  Eyewitnesses say he was not struggling with theofficer when he was shot.  Yong Xin was approximately 5'5" and weighed115 pounds at the time of his murder.  Despite a medical report andeyewitnesses that show Yong Xin was murdered in col d blood, theBrooklyn DA's office of Charles Hynes failed to indict Steven Mizrahi.Since its failure to indict in both cases, the Brooklyn DA's office hasnot made any effort to follow-up with either family. They haverepeatedly ignored both families' demands for justice. We unde rstandthat it is the responsibility of the DA's office to advocate on behalfof victims of brutal and racist violence. Hynes's failure to respond toeither family is indicative of a system which in variably turns it backwhen young people of color are murdered by police.  ONLY TWO NYC POLICEOFFICERS HAVE BEEN INDICTED FOR COMMITTING HOMICIDE WHILE ON DUTY IN THELAST 5 YEARS.  In 1994 alone, 60 police killings of people of color werereported.  Yet since 1977, only one officer has been convicted.Charles Hynes, Mayor Rudolph Giuliani, and Police Commissioner WilliamBratton would like to erase the state-sanctioned murder of Yong Xin andAnibal from our minds and memories.  Approximately one y ear since themurder of both youths, the families and friends of our two youngbrothers occupied the Brooklyn DA's office so that no one will forgetthe names of these two young men--another step in the struggle forjustice.Hyne's office was occupied at 11 am.  Press covering the sit-in wasbarred from the area. Reporters were kept behind a glass partition downthe hall from the sit-in.  At one point, Assistant DA's and cops triedto cover the glass partition with cardboard so that the press couldn'ttake pictures.  The DA's office refused to talk with reporters andinstead shoved a bundle of hastily-written press releases under theglass partition behind which the reporters had been corralled.  (Thereleases said there was no need for another Grand Jury.)  Dozens of riotpolice, emergency service units, and t hree swat teams were mobilizedagainst the non-violent demonstration.After more than three hours, the demonstrators, who were represented bylawyer Ron Kuby, were arrested.  Those arrested included the mother ofAnibal Carrasquillo and Yong Xin Huang's two sisters.In the paddy wagon as we were being taken to the precinct, demonstratorscontinued to chant "No Justice, No Peace!"  We were booked, charged with*obstructing governmental administration in the seco nd degree,*criminal trespass in the third degree, an *disorderly conduct.  We haveto appear in court on April 15, 1996 (120 Schermerhorn St., Part AP 1,9:30 am).This marks the first time, government officials in NYC have arrested theFAMILIES of police brutality victims during a protest.  In October 1995,there was a sit-in at the Bronx DA's office by the fa milies of AnthonyBaez, killed by a police chokehold, and Anthony Rosario and Hilton Vega,shot in the back a total of 22 times by police officers.  In thataction, protestors charged that the Bronx DA, Robert Johnson, sabotagedthe case against Frank Livoti, the officer who killed Anthony Baez,first through a bogus "typographical error" and later by refusing thefamily's request that he reindi ct Livoti.  The Bronx DA and policethere refused to arrest the family members and their supporters.  Twoweeks later, Livoti was re-indicted.  (The October sit-in in the BronxDA's office and the re cent sit-in in the Brooklyn DA's office bothreceived extensive media coverage.)The families of Anibal Carrasquilo, Yong Xin Huang, Anthony Baez,Anthony Rosario, a nd Hilton Vega will be in the contingent that willlead the RACIAL JUSTICE DAY rally on March 28, 1996."When a cop is shot in the back, it's murder; and when a cop shootssomeone in the back, it's STILL murder."         -Milta Calderon (mother of Anibal Carrasquillo)</PRE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
