iends and neighbors to distribute flyers with his son's photo. Brianis protesting the seizure of 35 Canadian computers by U.S., Customs onJanuary 31.While spirits are high among the five fasters, unusually cold weatherhas taken a physical toll, Weight loss to date is as high as 10 pounds,The fasters are living in a plastic and canvas "chapel" located at theU.S.Mexico border. The "Wayside Chapel of Peace and Friendship" offersscant protection from heavy rains and high winds."The Cuban people suffer the consequences of the embargo every day,"said Jim Clifford, a member of the fast. "The sacrifice we make is smallin comparison."</PRE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
