<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: High School Student March Against Utah Anti-Gay Ban on School Clubs</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/repsban.gif" ALT="Reports" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><H3>HIGH SCHOOL STUDENT MARCH AGAINST UTAH ANTI-GAY BAN ON SCHOOL CLUBS</H3><PRE>February 23Hundred of Salt Lake City High School students marched to the StateCapitol today to protest the city's ban on extracurricular clubs.  TheBoard of Education passed the ban to prevent gay and lesbian supportgroups from meeting at high schools.  Such clubs would otherwise haveprotected by the Federal Equal Access Act of 1984, an act passed byconservatives with the intention of shielding Bible clubs.  Utah'sSenator Orrin Hatch, a sponsor of the FEAA stated last week "The act wasnever intended to promulgate immoral speech or activity".While there were no arrests at the march, a 14-year-old girl was hit bya car and seriously injured.</PRE> </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
