<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Demo Against Psychiatric "Assault"</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/notiban.gif" ALT="Notices" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD>
<H3>Saturday, July 27, California Demo Against Psychiatric "Assault"</H3><PRE>

Dear people concerned about human rights in psychiatry:

Suspicious deaths, restraints, corruption... East Bay Hospital
has it all, and the silence will be broken.

Network Against Psychiatric Assault (NAPA) is a sponsoring group of
Support Coalition. They are planning an important protest
in Richmond, California, Saturday, July 27 at 1:30.  Below is an
announcement from long-time psychiaric survivor activist
and attorney, Ted Chabasinski.

Mon., July 29 is the scheduled beginning of the trial on the wrongful
death lawsuit.


---------- Forwarded message ----------
Date: Tue Jul 2 13:46:22 1996
From: Ted Chabasinski <sfletch@earthlink.com>
To: dendron@efn.org
Subject: NAPA campaign against local snake pit

Hello-- I wanted to make sure you folks know about the Network
Against Psychiatric Assault demonstration against East Bay
Hospital in Richmond, California.

There have been a number of unexplained deaths there, also people
tied naked to beds, crammed into overcrowded wards with nothing
at all to do, drugged into a stupor.

One woman became partially paralyzed after she was given a
botched shot of psychiatric drugs against her will.  She
complained to staff for weeks that she couldn't walk, but they
said it was all in her head.  Three weeks later, she had a
seven-hour operation to repair her spine, but it was too late.

Another patient arrived at the hospital apparently suffering from
an overdose of psychiatric drugs.  East Bay Hospital treated this
with massive doses of more drugs.  The patient died in
restraints.  The hospital record claimed he had been checked
every 15 minutes, as state law requires.  The record indicated he
was "resting quietly" or "sleeping" up to two minutes before his
death was discovered.  When found, his body was in a state of
rigor mortis, which takes several hours after death to develop.
A trial on the wrongful death lawsuit brought by his family is
scheduled to begin Monday, July 29.

Conditions at the hospital were exposed by a newspaper put out by
the American Friends Service Committee.

The demonstration is at 1:30 on Saturday July 27.  It is expected
to be the beginning of a difficult campaign to close down this
terrible place, which is privately owned but supported almost
entirely by public funds.  Its director is a family member of a
local Superior Court judge;  one of the two psychiatrists who own
it is reputed to have close ties with Governor Pete Wilson.
Attempts by licensing inspectors to close the place down in 1992,
after many violations were found, were thwarted when word came
down from Sacramento (the state capitol) to leave them alone.

For more info, contact Ted Chabasinski at (510) 843-6372, or send
e-mail to sfletch@earthlink.com.


~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

