<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Earth First Announces 1996 Action</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/notiban.gif" ALT="Notices" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD>
<H3>September 15 - 22, Earth First! Announces 96 Action</H3><PRE>
I realize that the Headwaters Forest is not technically a "salvage sale"
nor is it technically "public land"--as much as I think such
distinctions are meaningless anyway--it is nevertheless in danger again
and Charles Hurwitz *does* owe the people much money for his junk bond
scandals and so forth so with that in mind:

+++++ DEFEND HEADWATERS FOREST +++++
++++++ Summer 1996 - Northern California ++++++

(Ecotopia) Earth First! is putting out a call this summer to defend the
last redwood wilderness.  Once again, Maxxam has the legal okay to
invade the Headwaters ancient groves for "salvage logging" this
September 15, and we intend to foil their plans for the second year in a
row.  Meanwhile, they are continuing their plans for the second year in
a row.  Meanwhile, they are continuing their massacre of the 45,000
acres of old growth and second growth redwood that connect the ancient
groves.  Cutting in these areas will be going on all summer.
   We are planning week-long action campaigns in july and August to
protest this continuing slaughter and remind Maxxam why they need to get
out of Headwaters.  Then it's on to a full-scale mobolization for
September 15, when marbled murrelet nesting season ends and Maxxam's
salvage logging assault on the pristine Headwaters ancient redwood grove
is scheduled to begin.
   Last September 15, two thousand people rallied to save Headwaters and
264 were arrested in a mass civil disobedience, followed by two solid
months of tree-sits, lock-downs, and blockades in the woods.  In the
midst of the large demonstration, the court granted a restraining order
to stop Maxxam's salvage logging in the entire 50,000-acre Headwaters
complex.  But this spring, with the protesters gone, the appeals court
overturned the restraining order.  We will have to mobolize even more
people this year to stop them again.  Base camp will open September 13
and continue until we shut Maxxam down.
   This is a high-stakes battle, being fought over the survival of
2000-year old redwoods that are threatened by the greed of junk-bond
corporate raider Charles Hurwitz.  But our actions in Headwaters are
neither symbolic nor futile.  In fact, we are on the brink of victory.
After nine years of blockades, lawsuits, legislations and mass campaigns
by Earth First!, EPIC, and others, Maxxam's president Charles Hurwitz is
finally ready to give in.  He has publicly stated that he is now willing
to sell.  And, as pressure mounts for a debt-for-nature swap, and court
rulings limit his ability to cut, Hurwitz has recently filed a lawsuit
demanding that the government pay him for Headwaters Forest if they will
not let him log it.
   But even while he is trying to arrange a sale, Hurwitz is still
cutting away, taking out as many trees and as much profit as he can
before he gives up the land.  So this is a race to the finish line.  If
we keep up the pressure, this precious and irreplaceable forest can
actually be saved.  If we back down now, we could lose it all.  See you
in the woods this summer!

For more information, contact Ecotopia Earth First!

+ Humboldt County - (707) 923-3366
+ Mendocino County - (707) 459-4110
+ Bay Area Earth First! - (510) 848-8724
+ San Francisco - (415) 332-5800
+ Santa Cruz Earth First! - (408) 425-3205
+ E-mail - force.ten@lbbs.org

What to bring....

   Bushwacking through redwood country can be a miserable experience
without the right gear.  Good hiking boots are a must, along with a
water bottle, sturdy clothing for cold wet nights (hat, jacket, and
gloves) and hot days, and a small pack for food and equipment (CB,
flashlight, ets.).  Tape recorders and video cameras are also useful to
document police abuses if they occur.  At basecamp you'll need your own
dish and utensils, sleeping gear and a tent or some kind of rain
protection.  Bring some bulk food to donate to the communal kitchen, and
musical instruments and songbooks for campfire singing.

What NOT to bring.... Guns, dogs, illegal drugs.

Non-violence code:

   Earth First! actions in the Ecotopia region are bsed on
mass-organizing principals that include a specific non-violence code.

+ No violence, verbal or physical.
+ No weapons
+ No drugs or alchohol
+ No sabotage or property damage
+ and ABSOLUTELY no tree spiking!

There are rational and justifiable explanations for our positions on
these issues, and we are willing to discuss the various reasons for
being non-violent, though these principals are not negotiable.

We also encourage folks to come with an affinity group of people that
you know and trust for your own safety and security on actions.  While
blockades are usually exciting and fun, this is not a picnic and
tensions are high.  We must remember that some of the people we will
encounter, particularly the loggers are exploited as much as the forest
by the same corporations (in this case MAxxam) and no matter how
confused they may be, THEY ARE NOT THE ENEMY.  Furthermore, COINTELPRO
type tactics  have plagued us in the past and may do so again.  Violence
can be easily exploited by provocateurs and completely sabotage a
successful blockade.  If you are not prepared to adhere to the
non-violence code, then please don't come.

There will be three different series of actions:

+ July 19-25 & August 16-22 - Base camp open for woods actions in the
Headwaters Forest complex.
+ Sept 13 - ? - Base camp open for massive actions to defend Headwaters
ancient groves from salvage logging set to begin Sept. 15th.

There WILL be a massive rally on September 15th.

If you're interested, send the following information to Earth First!,
316 South Main Street, Willits, CA 95490 or call any of the listed phone
numbers.

Name_______________
Address___________________
Phone____________________
[]July 19-25   []August 16-22 []September 13-?
[]Donation $_____

If you wish to distribute (hard-copy) bunches of this announcement,
please send a request to the address listed above; and please copy this
post to everyone on your lists!

      Abolish the wage/rent/prison system! <a href="http://www.iww.org/">http://www.iww.org</a>

to:   INT:wall-list@igc.apc.org
