<H3>Wednesday, September 25, National Day of Action v. Corporate Greed</H3><PRE>NATIONAL DAY OF ACTION AGAINST CORPORATE GREED

Distributed at Jobs With Justice national meeting, June 28-30
University of Washington, Seattle, Washington

*********************************************

On September 25, 1996, Jobs with Justice will coordinate national actions
around the country to oppose excessive executive compensation,
layoffs/downsizing and the abuse of workers.  Under a unifying banner of,
"Stop Corporate Greed - We want Jobs with Justice," unions and local JwJ
coalitions would select specific corporate targets.

Corporate greed that emanates from the boardrooms of Wall Street
eventually makes its way to the Main Street, as time and time again
corporations disregard worker health and safety, abuse workers' rights to
organize and avail themselves of public subsidies to support their
private profits.  Rampant corporate greed has CEO'S, Wall Street and
their complicit Congressional cronies singing, "don't worry - be happy"
while the rest of us are singing the blues.

Unions and communities can no longer sit back -- We have to fight back.
Jobs with Justice local coalitions working with unions, community and
religious organizations hope to help lead the charge on corporate greed.

Actions are now being planned in cities all across the country.  If you
want to be a part of this exciting mobilization, please fill out the form
below and mail or fax it to the national Jobs with Justice office, 501
Third Street, NW, Washington, DC 20001, 202-434-1106 PHONE/202-434-1482
FAX.  We'll let you know if an action is being planned in your community
or how you can organize one.

***********************************************

Yes, sign me up.  I want to be part of the National Day of Action!

____I can lead an action.

____I can assist with an action.

Name:

Address:

City/State/Zip:

Phone/Fax/Email:



Send to:
Jobs with Justice
501 Third Street, NW, #872
Washington, DC 20001
202-434-1106 PHONE
202-434-1482 FAX

