<H3>Activists Needed at Olympics</H3><PRE>WE WON'T BE PLAYING GAMES FOR THE SUMMER GAMES!

VOLUNTEERS NEEDED June 30, to Aug. 5, 1996 To
STAND UP FOR FREEDOM IN ATLANTA

Wanted: Disciplined, Committed and Conscious Organizers.  To work for the
human rights and self-determination of the Black nation, during the 1996
Summer Games in Atlanta.  Let the World know that We are a colonized New
Afrikan nation fighting for human rights and self-determination.  Take the
covers off the lie of the White Power Government!  Take the Black case for
Genocide and Human Rights violations against the United States before the
World!

Sleeping Spaces and other accommodations will be provided.  Bring your
sleeping bags.

To Sign-up Call the Malcolm X Center for Self-determination:
(404) 288-9880.

Sponsored by The Coalition for New Afrikan Human Rights and
Self-determination.

Endorsed by:  New Afrikan Liberation Front; National Coalition of Blacks for
Reparations in America; Provisional Government-Republic of New Afrika;
Malcolm X Grassroots Movement.


Makungu M. Akinyela, Ph.D.

I believe in the family and the community,
and in the community as a family, and I
will work to make this concept live.

                               Point Two of the
                               New Afrikan Creed.

