<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Call for Ohio Death Penalty Activists</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/notiban.gif" ALT="Notices" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD>
<H3>Call for Ohio Death Penalty Activists</H3><PRE>Ohio activists, where are you?  Ohio could soon begin resumption of
executions.  A prisoner on Ohio's death row has recently terminated
his appeals process.  A court has determined that he was adequately
competent to make the decision.  Therefore, the execution parade could
soon begin in Ohio.

Marianne, at gumby1618@aol.com is interested in working with other
Ohio activists to coordinate a massive vigil to protest the resumption
of executions in Ohio.  She needs your help.  If you are in Ohio (or
anywhere in the proximity, please send an email to Marianne (you can
cc: me).  Many organizers will be needed to make this proposed activity
most effective.

Ohio, like my own state of NJ, has the death penalty but has yet to
resume executions.  It is important for us to draw a line in states
where executions have yet to begin, to do everything in our power to
prevent especially the first one.  If there is no first execution,
there can be no second or third, etc.

You can begin to help the Ohio mobilization effort by forwarding this
email message to as many appropriate networks as possible, and particularly
to concerned Ohio residents.

LET'S DRAW THE LINE!  LET'S STOP THE EXECUTIONS BEFORE THEY START!

If we can succeed in any one state in preventing a FIRST execution, we
can begin to turn the tide against the death march across this nation.
Such an experience for the Death Penalty Abolitionist Movement would
prove that we do in fact have the power to fight and win this
important battle.

>From Ohio, to New Jersey, to Texas, to California, let us unite,
let us fight, let us be victorious in our struggle to end the death
penalty.

LET'S GET BUSY!!!

Bob Witanek, NJ Coalition Against the Death Penalty</PRE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
