<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: An American Tradition: Protest</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/newsbut.gif" ALT="NEWS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/commban.gif" ALT="Commentary" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><H3>AN AMERICAN TRADITION: PROTEST</H3>by the ACLU<P><I>April 4, 1995 </I><P>On Tuesday, March 21, an estimated 10,000 students and faculty membersfrom the City University of New York system and area high schools attendeda largely peaceful rally called to demonstrate displeasure with theeducation budget cuts and higher tuition proposed by New York GovernorGeorge E. Pataki and New York City Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani. <P>Commenting on the demonstration, Mayor Giuliani said about the students,"They're supposed to be in class today and they're not.  And they are notpaying for their own education.  Somebody else is paying for it."  He wenton to suggest that the protesters' time would be better spent looking forjobs to pay for their education. <P>Aside from ignoring the fact that most CUNY students come fromlower-income families and, thus, hold jobs while they are pursuing aneducation -- which means they are taxpayers who do contribute to the costof their schooling -- the Mayor was also off base in suggesting that thestudents and their teachers had no business making their voices heard onpublic policy initiatives that directly affect their lives.  Thus did hetrash, by implication, a hallowed American tradition: the right toprotest. <P>The First Amendment to our Constitution guarantees the freedom of speech,which is the bedrock of American liberty.  David Buchbinder, a parent whoescorted some children from one of the city's elementary schools to therally, put it well: The rally, he said, was "an exercise in representativedemocracy." <P>Mayor Giuliani could use a refresher course on the Bill of Rights.<P><I>"Eternal vigilance is the price of liberty"</I></BLOCKQUOTE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
