<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Motion To Dismiss: Police Officer Did Not Appear</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/refsbut.gif" ALT="REFERENCES" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/legaban.gif" ALT="Legal Materials" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><H3>Motion To Dismiss: Police Officer Did Not Appear</H3><BLOCKQUOTE><I>Here is an excerpt of a motion to dismiss a Disorderly Conduct charge in the Summons Part on the grounds that the police officer did not appear in court to testify within 30 days of the defendants first court appearance.<P></I><P></BLOCKQUOTE><HR><BLOCKQUOTE>CRIMINAL COURT OF THE CITY OF NEW YORK<BR>COUNTY OF NEW YORK: SUMMONS PART<P>THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEW YORK,<P>		   -against-                      <P>PAUL DEAN,                              	Docket No. 94N039310<P>                   Defendant.<P>....	I.	MOTION TO DISMISS THE INFORMATION BASED ON CPL 30.30<P>	The Criminal Procedure Law sets forth the number of days within which the prosecution must be ready to proceed against a defendant, failing which the case must be dismissed.<P>	In cases in which the highest allegation against the defendant is a violation, the prosecution must be ready to proceed within 30 days from the commencement of the criminal action.  C.P.L. Sec. 30.30(1)(d).  <P>	The 30 day period starts at the defendants first appearance in court (&quot;where a defendant has been served with an appearance ticket, the criminal action must be deemed to have commenced on the date the defendant first appears in a a local criminal court in response to the ticket&quot; C.P.L. Sec. 30.30(5)(b)).<P>	In this case, the defendant is charged with a violation, Disorderly Conduct, therefore the prosecution had to proceed within 30 days.  Defendant's first day in court was January 20, 1995, therefore the prosecution had to take place on or before February 19, 1995.  On February 15, the 26th day after the commencement of the case, the police officer did not come to court and the case was adjourned to March 10th.  On March 10th, it will be 46 days since the commencement of the case, well over the 30-day limit set by C.P.L. Sec. 30.30(1)(d). <P>	Therefore, since the prosecution has not proceeded within 30 days of the commencement of the case, the charges must be dismissed.<P>Dated:  New York, New York<BR>	   March 3, 1995<P>							_____________________________<BR>								ATTORNEY FOR DEFENDANT<P></BLOCKQUOTE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
