<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: 240.20  Disorderly Conduct</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/refsbut.gif" ALT="REFERENCES" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/legaban.gif" ALT="Legal Materials" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><H3>Pertinent Statute: 240.20  Disorderly Conduct</H3><HR><BLOCKQUOTE>A person is guilty of disorderly conduct when, with intent to cause public inconvenience, annoyance or alarm, or recklessly creating a risk thereof:<BR><OL><LI>He engages in fighting or in violent, tumultuous or threatening behavior; or<BR><LI>He makes unreasonable noise; or<BR><LI>In a public place, he uses abusive or obscene language, or makes an obscene gesture; or<BR><LI>Without lawful authority, he disturbs any lawful assembly or meeting of persons; or<BR><LI>He obstructs vehicular or pedestrian traffic; or<BR><LI>He congregates with other persons in a public place and refuses to comply with a lawful order of the police to disperse; or<BR><LI>He creates a hazardous or physically offensive condition by any act which serves no legitimate purpose.</OL>  Disorderly conduct is a violation.<P></BLOCKQUOTE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
