<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Demonstrator's Site: Riot In The Second Degree</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#D90000" ALINK="#FFFF00"><CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=500><TR><TD><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/refsbut.gif" ALT="REFERENCES" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=90><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../gifs/legaban.gif" ALT="Legal Materials" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=410 HSPACE=0><P></TD></TR><TR><TD><H3>Pertinent Statute: Riot In The Second Degree</H3><HR><BLOCKQUOTE>  A person is guilty of riot in the second degree when, simultaneously with four or more other persons, he engages in tumultuous and violent conduct and thereby intentionally or recklessly causes or creates a grave risk of causing public alarm.<P>  Riot in the second degree is a class A misdemeanor.<P></BLOCKQUOTE></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../../gifs/backbar.gif" ALT="BACK" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
