<TITLE>Getting your own Home Page at...</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="ffffff" text="000044" link="0000ff" vlink="660099">

<A HREF="index.html">
<img src="home_btn.gif" 
     hspace=5
     align="middle" 
     alt="HOME">

VILLAGE Home Page
</A> 

<p>
<img src="/icons/line_sun.gif" alt="----------">
<p>

<H2>PDE's INFORMATION VILLAGE CONCEPT</H2><p>

The Internet has been described as a massive, world-wide library of 
information that is not well organized or catalogued. In other words, 
information can be difficult to find. Our specialty at PDE Publications is to make your home page part of a specialized traffic safety &quot;information 
village&quot; that will quickly become known on the Net as the place to go for 
this kind of information. Browsers with an interest in this topic will find 
the village easily and return to it again and again to check what's new. <p>


The Village consists of Home Pages (Web sites) and a database with free and restricted areas. The free browsing area has interesting articles and news about driver behaviour, traffic safety and education. The restricted area has a password for paying subscribers and offers access to in-depth articles, conference proceedings, periodicals, abstracts and reference materials for traffic safety professionals.<p>

The concept of the Village is to create a networked community of individuals, groups, businesses and organizations with a common interest in traffic safety.<p>

<H3>YOUR HOME PAGE</H3><p>


To get your home page up on the WWW as part of the PDE Traffic Safety 
Information Village, contact us at:<p>


<strong>
PDE Publications Inc.<BR>
5334 Yonge St., Suite 310<BR>
Toronto, Ontario, Canada M2N 6M2
<P> 
Tel: (416) 767-4885<BR>
Fax: (416) 767-7425<BR>
E-Mail:<a href="mailto:pde@drivers.com">pde@drivers.com</a>
</strong>



