<H1>PDE PUBLICATIONS INC.</H1>

<H3>... the Traffic Safety Information Village</H3>

<img src="/icons/line_sun.gif" alt="----------">
<p>


<strong>PDE Publications Inc.<BR>3266 Yonge St., Suite 1921<BR>
Toronto, Ontario, 
Canada M4N 3P6</strong>
<P> 
Tel: (416) 767-4885<BR>
Fax: (416) 767-7425<BR>
E-Mail: <a href="mailto:pde@drivers.com">pde@drivers.com</a>


<P>

<H3>What is PDE?</H3>

<P> PDE Publications Inc. is a knowledge-based company specializing in driver 
education and traffic safety. With a host site on the Internet's World Wide Web, 
PDE is a global corporation in every sense of the word. While its officers 
and employees are physically located in Toronto, Canada, this is almost 
meaningless in an age where bits of digital information are exchanged 
between computers at nearly light speed. As far as PDE's clients are 
concerned, the company might as well be in London, Geneva, Reykjavik or 
Perth, Australia.

<P> PDE is served by dedicated specialists with many years' experience in 
traffic safety. This experience and knowledge is backed 
by journalistic and computer skills.

<P> PDE Publications is setting up an electronic information resource for 
researchers, policymakers, public speakers and practitioners in traffic 
safety and related fields. It provides one-stop shopping for anyone browsing 
the Internet for information on these subjects.

<P> The company's objective is to disseminate information in this important 
area and provide a meeting of minds for both professionals and 
non-professionals.  There are millions of drivers out there and lots of 
topics of keen interest to both layman and professional.

<P> PDE makes no apologies for being a commercial enterprise. At the same 
time, in the true spirit of the Internet, we provide several free categories 
on our menu for casual browsers, including a regular updated News section, a 
list of upcoming events such as international conferences and seminars, 
names and addresses of prominent organizations.

<P> We are open to casual browsers. However, if you want access to our 
database, it pays to be a subscriber. Our fee to subscribers is $55 U.S. ($75 Can.) 
per year for individuals, $95 U.S. ($128 Can.) for organizations. This fee 
gives unlimited downloading of articles, reports, summaries and 
newsletters.

<P> Once we receive your subscription cheque or money order, we issue you 
with a password to give you full access to our database.<p>

<H3>The Wave of the Future</H3>

<P> By now you must be saturated with all the Internet hype in the news 
media.  Remember that the Internet is just another tool -- a very powerful 
one, but a tool nevertheless. In the case of PDE, we are using the World 
Wide Web to sell knowledge products and create a marketplace -- an 
"information village" if you wish - where anyone who is connected with 
driving or traffic safety can meet to learn and to discuss ideas.

<P> Many of the professionals among you go to conferences and seminars. 
Well, here's a seminar you can join anytime you have half an hour to spare. 
In addition, in our Articles database, we hope to provide you with 
information you can use in preparing your own reports and speeches.

<P> Neither is the flow of information intended to be one-way. If you, in 
turn, have prepared a report or speech and would like the world to see it, 
send it to us for consideration for our database.

<P> Remember, the World Wide Web knows no boundaries. It cuts across all 
borders and jurisdictions and it just as easily cuts through red tape. Here 
is a truly democratic way to participate in this exciting area.

<p>
<img src="/icons/line_sun.gif" alt="----------">
<p>




