<H3>Parents:</H3>
<blockquote>
Is your teenager about to drive? Remember, auto accidents are the number-one cause of death in teenagers. Give yourself and your teenager some peace of mind with the added protection of the <STRONG>Peace of Mind Sign</STRONG>. <P>

Your teen may feel a little uncomfortable with this sign on the car but, as a parent, you should insist on its use during practice sessions with your new driver. Take a lesson from driving schools. These organizations use warning signs on their vehicles to improve communication with other drivers and to help ensure the safety of their students. Now you can offer your child that same protection. Don't hesitate a minute when you can maximize the safety of your child. <P>
</blockquote>
<H3>Provide a better practice environment</H3>
<blockquote>
Provide your new driver with a "cushion of safety." The <STRONG>Peace of Mind 
Sign</STRONG> can easily prevent an accident by simply alerting other vehicles to your situation.  It will help prevent tailgating, horn honking, altercations with other drivers. It relieves much of the stress for driver and parent.<P>
</blockquote>
