<html><head>
<title>GRADUATED LICENSING FOR SENIORS</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>GRADUATED LICENSING FOR SENIORS</h2>
<p>There's strong evidence that the skills
needed for safe driving begin to decline around age 55 and then drop off
more dramatically after age 75. Licensing systems that would ease aging
drivers out of driving privileges in the same fashion that novices are
eased in are gaining in support. A recent article in the September/October
issue of the national Safety Council's Traffic Safety Magazine describes
some of the difficulties of developing such systems, and the advantages.
The American Association for Retired Persons  favors a system based on
abilities rather than age.
<p>
<i>
</i><p>
