<html><head>
<title>ENFORCEMENT AND DUI</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>ENFORCEMENT AND DUI</h2>
<p>There are a variety of reasons why police officers
might want to go easy on intoxicated drivers: They see them as "average
people" rather than criminals; DUI arrests are among the most
time-consuming misdemeanour arrests and often officers have to go to court
in their own time; and penalties are stiffer and defendants typically mount
more vigorous defenses. Former Michigan trooper Dennis F. Bryde of Michigan
State University teaches a course that helps police officers deal with the
problems of DUI enforcement.

<p>
<i>
</i><p>
