<html><head>
<title>SAFEST CARS, AND WORST</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>SAFEST CARS, AND WORST</h2>
<p>Bigger is better and airbags are critical, concludes
a recent survey of automobile safety conducted by the U.S. Insurance
Insititute for Highway Safety (IIHS). Cars, utility vehicles, pickups, and
passenger vans were surveyed. The Geo Tracker had the worst record at 3.2
deaths per 10,000 registered vehicles. The Volvo 240 and the Saab 9000
topped the list. The survey is reported in the October 14 issue of the IIHS
Status reports.
<p>
