<H1>Video Resources</H1>
<H3>NOTE: This article was originally part of PDE's &quot;Guide to Resources&quot;, which was published in 1994.</H3>

<blockquote>This section of the <STRONG>Guide to Resources</STRONG> started out as an attempt to develop a &quot;top 20&quot; list of videos, but that turned out to be impractical. The information was difficult to get and video catalogues tended to have many titles that were very out of date. <p>
The best alternative seemed to be to ask a cross-section of driver educators from across the U.S. and Canada what videos they use and which ones they would recommend. The results are summarized below. <p>
However, it quickly became obvious that, for the most part, driver educators haven't been buying many new videos. Most of those recommended were more than five years old, and many were more than ten. Money for new purchases has been scarce and there haven't been many new videos available until recently. <p>
The survey turned into two listings: 10 videos widely used in the U.S., and 10 widely used in Canada. A separate listing for Canada is included because there are some good Canadian videos available that seem to be little known in the U.S. There were a total of 27 respondents to the survey, which was quite informal, so not too much significance should be given to the selection. It was just a way to get a measure of what's out there. <p>
More importantly, a listing of videos produced since 1990 will give readers an idea of what new offerings are available. <P>
</blockquote>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="contents">CONTENTS
</A></H3><UL><LI><STRONG><A HREF="#used1">What's being used: U.S.</A></STRONG><P><LI>
<STRONG><A HREF="#used2">What's being used: Canada</A></STRONG><P><LI>
<STRONG>What's new (after 1990) from...<P>
</STRONG><UL><LI><A HREF="#aaaf">The AAA Foundation for Traffic Safety</A><LI>
<A HREF="#aaa">The AAA</A><LI>
<A HREF="#safety">Safety Industries Incorporated</A><LI>
<A HREF="#care">The Car Care Council</A><LI>
<A HREF="#mano">The Manocherian Foundation</A><LI>
<A HREF="#lifesaver">Operation Lifesaver Inc.</A><LI>
<A HREF="#challenge">The Ultimate Driving Challenge</A><LI>
<A HREF="#highway">The Insurance Institute for Highway Safety</A><LI>
<A HREF="#vision">The Center for Unlimited Vision</A><LI>
<A HREF="#systems">Interactive Driving Systems</A><LI>
<A HREF="#cyrs">Cyr's Driving School</A></UL></UL>

<HR>
<H3><A NAME="used1">WHAT'S BEING USED: U.S.</A></H3>

The videos listed below are the 10 most often recommended and are not listed with any priority. <P>
<blockquote>
<STRONG>Get a Grip</STRONG> (Goodyear, 1992): Wet weather driving. How tires work on wet surfaces <A HREF="#grip">(see below)</A>.<P>

<STRONG>Just Another Friday Night </STRONG>(AAA, 1984): Drunk driving trial. Good discussion video.<P>

<STRONG>Room to Live II </STRONG>(1982): Older movie but a very strong message about seatbelt use. <P>

<STRONG>Taking Care of It </STRONG>(Ford, 1986): Shows under-the-hood checks and meaning of warning lights. <P>

<STRONG>The Aftermath</STRONG> (1990): Drinking and driving <A HREF="#aftermath">(see below)</A>.<P>

<STRONG>The Ultimate Driving Challenge</STRONG> (GM, 1993): <A HREF="#ultimate">See below</A>.<P>

<STRONG>To Drive at Night</STRONG> (AAA,1976): Visual problems, need to modify driving habits. <P>

<STRONG>Visual Perception in Driving</STRONG> (AAA, 1981): Parts I &#38; II of a two-part series demonstrating that visual perception in driving is more than just seeing.<P>

<STRONG>WaterSkiing on Four Wheels</STRONG> (AAA, 1978): Dangers of hydroplaning and techniques for driving in wet weather. <P>

<STRONG>Your Cushion for Safety </STRONG>(1982): How to apply the five rules of the Smith System of Space Cushion Driving.<P>
<A HREF="#contents">RETURN</A> to Table of Contents<P></blockquote>
<HR><P>
<H3><A NAME="used2">WHAT'S BEING USED: CANADA</A></H3>

The videos listed below are the ten most often recommended and are not listed with any priority.<P>
<blockquote>
<STRONG>Just Another Friday Night</STRONG> (AAA, 1984): Drunk driving trial. Good discussion video.<P>

<STRONG>Living With Trucks </STRONG>(Ontario MOT, 1988): Interaction between car drivers and truckers. <P>

<STRONG>Power Under Control: The Alcohol You</STRONG> (Ontario MOT, 1980): Uses actors and cartoon characters to portray the effects of alcohol on the mental and physical task of driving. <P>

<STRONG>Taking Care of It </STRONG>(Ford, 1986): Shows under-the-hood checks and meaning of warning lights. <P>

<STRONG>The Ultimate Driving Challenge</STRONG> (G.M., 1993): Interactive quiz format (<A HREF="#ultimate">see below</A>).<P>

<STRONG>To Drive at Night</STRONG> (AAA,1976): Visual problems, need to modify driving habits. <P>

<STRONG>Turning Left Right</STRONG> (L&#38;M Media, 1988) Explores problems of making left turns at traffic lights.<P>

<STRONG>Visual Perception in Driving</STRONG> (AAA, 1981): Parts I &#38; II of a two-part series demonstrating that visual perception in driving is more than just seeing. <P>

<STRONG>WaterSkiing on four Wheels</STRONG> (1979): Dangers of hydroplaning and techniques for driving in wet weather. <P>

<STRONG>Your Cushion for Safety</STRONG> (1982) How to apply the five rules of the Smith System of Space Cushion Driving.<P>

<P>
<A HREF="#contents">RETURN</A> to Table of Contents<P>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<H3><A NAME="new">WHAT'S NEW</A> (AFTER 1990)</H3>


<STRONG><A NAME="aaaf">FROM:</A> </STRONG><BR> The AAA Foundation For Traffic Safety<BR>1730 M Street N.W., Suite 401<BR>Washington D.C. 20036. <BR>
Tel: (202) 638-5944.<BR>
 Fax: (202) 638-5943. <P>
<blockquote>
<STRONG>Sharing the Road</STRONG> (1994): 8 minutes, $40 U.S. Understanding the special concerns and dangers faced by different road users. <P>

<STRONG>Using Your Eyes Effectively</STRONG> (1994): 8 minutes, $40. Demonstrates best use of eyes while driving. Central and peripheral vision, effects of alcohol on vision. <P>

<STRONG>Breaking the Accident Chain of Events </STRONG>(1994): 8 minutes, $40. Vignettes dramatizing the chain of events leading up to a collision. Emphasizes alertness, politeness and decisiveness. <P>

<STRONG>Driving in Bad Weather</STRONG> (1994): 8 minutes, $40. Uses setting of TV newscast to dramatize effects of fog, dust, smoke, rain, snow and ice. Tips on bad weather maintenance. <P>

<STRONG>Night Driving</STRONG> (AAA, 1994): 8 minutes, $40. Effects of darkness on vision. Night driving tips and habits. <P>

<STRONG>Freeway Driving</STRONG> (AAA, 1994): 8 minutes, $40. Demonstrates quick thinking needed on freeways, merging, tips on freeway driving, exiting. <P>
<A HREF="#contents">RETURN</A> to Table of Contents<P>

</blockquote><HR><P>
<STRONG><A NAME="aaa">FROM:</a> </STRONG><BR>The AAA<BR>1000 AAA Drive<BR>Heathrow, Fl 32746-5063<BR>Tel: (407) 444-7960 (or your local AAA office).<P>
<blockquote>
<STRONG><A NAME="grip">Get a Grip</A></STRONG> (Goodyear/ADTSEA/AAA, 1992): 18 minutes, $9.95. How tires work on wet surfaces, wet weather driving technigues, skid control. Facilitator's guide available.<P>

<STRONG>Getting Safely Past the Orange Barrels </STRONG>(1992): 11 minutes, $40. Designed to reduce crashes around work zones.<P>

<STRONG>First on the Scene</STRONG> (1990): 7 minutes, $30. What to do when arriving at the scene of a crash. <P>

<STRONG>Managing Space and Time for Safe Driving</STRONG> (1991): 8 minutes, $40. How good drivers use their eyes and manage space around their cars. <P>
<A HREF="#contents">RETURN</A> to Table of Contents<P>
</blockquote>
<HR><P>
<STRONG><A NAME="safety">FROM:</A> </STRONG><BR>
Safety Industries Incorporated
<BR>P.O. Box 1137
<BR>McGill, NV 89318-9900
<BR>Tel: (702) 235-7766, Fax: (702) 235-7767.<p>
<blockquote>
<STRONG>Basic Car Control</STRONG> (1993): 10 minutes, $109.95 U.S. Covers basic maneuvers such as the three-point turn, techniques for reversing, and the &quot;universal truths&quot; of operating vehicles.<P>

<STRONG>Car Tours</STRONG> (1992): 10 minutes, $109.95. Researchers from the 25th century study a 20th century automobile. Demonstration of the basics of automobile instrumentation (interior and exterior) as presented by a futuristic &quot;space alien.&quot; <P>

<STRONG>The Physics of Driving</STRONG> (1992): 10 minutes, $109.95. A brilliant nerd student impresses his fellow students with demonstrations of how gravity, friction, momentum, etc., affect driving.<P>

<STRONG>Rural Driving</STRONG> (1992): 10 minutes, $109.95. Viewers are given a homegrown introduction to the dangers of rural driving by a farmer and his wife.<P>

<STRONG>Freeway Driving</STRONG> (1992): 11 minutes, $109.95. Doctors diagnose a young woman with a severe case of &quot;freeway phobia.&quot; Entertaining approach to freeway driving techniques. <P>

<STRONG>Signs and Signals</STRONG> (1992): 10 minutes, $109.95. Fast-paced video on understanding and getting information from highway signs and signals. (Quiz included) <P>

<STRONG>Right of Way </STRONG>(1992): 10 minutes, $109.95. Roadway etiquette in a wide variety of driving situations. <P>

<STRONG>Defensive Driving </STRONG>(1992): 10 minutes, $109.95. Humorous TV game show setting provides an entertaining approach to determining the best reactions to a variety of driving situations. <P>

<STRONG>Emergency Situations</STRONG> (1992): 10 minutes, $109.95. Describes some of the most common emergencies and recommends the proper reactions to minimize the chance of injury. Covers brake failure, accelerator sticking, etc.<P>

<STRONG>Paint on the Pavement</STRONG> (1992): 10 minutes, $109.95. What pavement markings mean and how they help make driving safer and smoother. <P>

<STRONG>Physical and Mental Conditions</STRONG> (1992): 10 minutes, $109.95. How mental and physical conditions affect the ability to drive a car. How good drivers control their emotions and manage their driving attitudes.<P>

<STRONG>Buying and Insuring a Car </STRONG>(1992): 10 minutes, $109.95. Often, facts about the real costs of owning a car are overlooked. This video presents the facts about buying, financing, maintaining and insuring a car. <P>
<A HREF="#contents">RETURN</A> to Table of Contents<P>
</blockquote>
