<h1>Driver/Education Newsletter</h1>
<h3>Volume 4, Issue No. 4, December 1994</h3>
<p><hr><p><B>Driver/Education</B> newsletter can be downloaded free 
of charge by all subscribers to PDE Publications Inc. Alternatively, a 
year's subscription (four issues sent through the mail) is available at a 
cost of $25 for individuals and $35 for institutions.
<P>For subscription 
details, see our <A HREF="order.html">ORDER FORM</A>.<P>

IF YOU LIKE what <strong>Driver/Education</strong> is trying to do, we need your support. The only financial support this publication gets is that offered by subscribers. The purpose of the publication is to provide an independent source of information to everyone with an interest in the improvement of drivers through training and education. We hope that you will renew your subscription this year, and also that you will encourage others to subscribe. <P>

COPYRIGHT law prohibits any reproduction of the contents of this publication without the permission of PDE Publications. However, in order to facilitate groups or organizations that would like to make it available to their members, special group subscription rates are available. Please <A HREF="mailto:pde@drivers.com">contact us</A> for information.<P>

MODERN COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY offers enormous potential for providing information. Anything you need to know could be at your fingertips, and at very little cost. Imagine being able to get just the information you need for your project or idea, delivered instantly to your home or business. Whatever your interest  in training and education, there'll be lots of info for you on the information highway. More about this in upcoming issues of Driver/Education. <P>


<P>
<HR>
<h2><A NAME="contents">Table of Contents</A></h2><P>
<blockquote>
<ul>
